          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Our co-founder spent her second trimester with feet so dry they cracked overnight. Every foot peel on the shelf had salicylic acid on the warning label. Her dermatologist said no. Her OB said no. She tried lotion. It didn't work.</p>"
          }
        },
        "p2": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>A friend in Seoul sent her a video of a goat milk foot mask — a soft sock filled with the kind of formula K-beauty had been quietly perfecting for years. Lactic acid from milk (the same compound foot peels use, but at a fraction of the intensity), niacinamide for skin barrier, glycerin for hydration. No salicylic, no glycolic, no fragrance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "h1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "After 18 months of formulation, we shipped Kneuro."
          }
        },
        "p3": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Same idea, made stateside, with a 5% niacinamide concentration our team obsessed over for months. The result is a 30-minute mask gentle enough for pregnancy, sensitive skin, and diabetic feet — but powerful enough that you'll see the difference before you take it off.</p>"
          }
        },
        "p4": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We are a small team. We answer our own customer emails. We don't run influencer drops. We sell one product because we believe one product, formulated honestly, beats a catalog of okay-ish ones. If we ever launch a second SKU, it'll be because customers asked us for it for six months straight.</p>"
          }
